settings.helpText: Describes your image for anyone who can't see it. This includes: search engines and people using screen-readers. If you leave this blank, the image title will be used for alt text.
Briefly summarise the main topic or contention of the article. Used primarily for SEO and social media sharing, but may also be used for content previews and other summary components.
Auto generated based on your title. Helps with SEO-friendly urls.
The visible text part that users will click on.
Used for title or aria-label attributes to give additional information and context to people with screenreaders. Also helpful for SEO.

content.value: My mama always said life was like a box of chocolates. You never know what you're gonna get.
You don't understand! I coulda had class. I coulda been a contender. I could've been somebody, instead of a bum, which is what I am.
Roads? Where we're going we don't need roads.
I'm walking here! I'm walking here!

Google Earth is amazing. They've photographed every road in the world and put them on the computer. You just type it in and you go there. You sit in front of the computer and you think, 'I can go anywhere in the world. Where shall I go?' And we all come to the same conclusion: 'My house.'

description.en-US: A scene from the Matrix. Neo is offered a choice: ignorance and safety, or knowledge and risk.
